[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2026[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 8: Generate care-team reports, run outcome correlation, and feed the institutional improvement loop.** The assistant is not a closed system. Care-team reports flow on a defined cadence (real-time alerts for escalation events; daily digests for high-acuity patients; weekly digests for the broader engaged population; monthly summaries for care-management leadership; quarterly aggregates for institutional clinical leadership). The outcome-correlation pipeline pulls subsequent encounter records, claims data, prescription fills, lab results, and patient-and-caregiver-reported outcomes against the assistant's coordination-decision records to estimate the assistant's contribution to outcomes including referral-closure rate, transition-of-care completion rate, medication-reconciliation accuracy, avoidable-readmission rate, total-cost-of-care, and patient-and-caregiver-reported coordination experience. The institutional improvement loop feeds findings back into the coordination-protocol library, the prompt and tool surface, the seam-detection rules, the per-cohort monitoring, and the integration-coverage roadmap. Skip this and the assistant operates without measurable care-team trust, without measurable outcome accountability, and without an institutional learning mechanism.
