[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2489[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Performance benchmarks (illustrative, your mileage varies substantially with population, integration coverage, and program design):**
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2490[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2491[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Metric | Pre-coordination-assistant baseline | Post-coordination-assistant (engaged members) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2492[0m:[38;5;10m[49m |--------|--------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------|
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2493[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Referral closure rate at 90 days | Often around 50-70% across many U.S. settings | 75-90% for engaged members |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2494[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Average days from referral order to scheduled visit | Often 14-30 days, longer in many specialties | Reduction of several days, varying by specialty |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2495[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Medication-reconciliation accuracy after discharge | Variable, often substantial discrepancies between hospital list and patient's actual regimen | Meaningful reduction in unreconciled discrepancies |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2496[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | 30-day readmission rate (high-risk cohorts) | Substantial baseline rate for HF, COPD, sepsis discharges | Modest reduction in engaged members; not a panacea |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2497[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Duplicate-referral rate | Often invisible | Made visible and reducible by the assistant |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2498[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Patient-and-caregiver coordination experience (CSAT) | Variable, often low for complex patients | Generally improved, often substantially for caregivers |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2499[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Caregiver burden (self-reported) | Variable, often elevated for complex caregivers | Modest reduction, with the largest reductions for the most complex caregivers |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2500[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Engagement attrition by 6 months | N/A | 25-45% (the central operational risk) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2501[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Per-active-member infrastructure cost | N/A | $4-12 per active member per month |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2502[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Care-management workforce cost vs. infrastructure cost | N/A | Workforce typically larger than infrastructure |
