[49m[38;5;10m+    2657[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2658[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Variations and Extensions
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2659[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2660[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Post-discharge coordination assistant for heart-failure readmission prevention.** A focused variant for the 30- to 90-day window after a heart-failure admission, with HF-specific transition-of-care protocols, daily weight-and-symptom check-ins, fluid-balance seam-detection rules, and tight integration with the patient's cardiology team and home-health agency. Often deployed as the first variant because the readmission-prevention business case is among the strongest in the category and the protocols are well-established.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2661[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2662[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Post-surgery coordination assistant for orthopedic, cardiac, or oncology procedures.** A focused variant for the post-procedure recovery window, with procedure-specific transition-of-care protocols, post-operative complication detection, follow-up appointment coordination, physical-therapy referral tracking, and tight integration with the surgical team and post-acute care providers.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2663[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2664[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Oncology-treatment coordination assistant.** A focused variant for patients in active cancer treatment, with treatment-cycle protocols, chemotherapy-cycle coordination, supportive-care navigation, palliative-care integration, and tight integration with the oncology team. Subject to the dense regulatory landscape around cancer care including state cancer-registry reporting where applicable.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2665[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2666[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Transplant-program coordination assistant.** A focused variant for transplant patients across the pre-transplant, peri-transplant, and post-transplant phases, with transplant-specific protocols including immunosuppressant management coordination, rejection-monitoring lab tracking, infection-prevention protocols, and tight integration with the transplant program. The architectural discipline is similar to the broader coordination assistant; the scope and clinical content are transplant-specific.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2667[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2668[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Pediatric complex-care coordination assistant.** A focused variant for pediatric patients with multiple complex chronic conditions, with parent-and-caregiver-as-primary-speaker design, school and developmental-services integration, pediatric-specific protocols, and tight integration with the pediatric medical-home model. State-specific adolescent-confidentiality rules apply for older pediatric patients.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2669[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2670[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Maternal-and-perinatal coordination assistant.** A focused variant for the prenatal, peri-natal, and post-partum windows, with prenatal-care coordination protocols, post-partum-discharge transitions, infant-care coordination, mental-health screening (PHQ-9, EPDS), social-determinant screening, and integration with the prenatal-and-post-partum care team.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2671[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2672[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Aging-in-place coordination assistant for older adults with multiple chronic conditions.** A focused variant for the broad Medicare population with multiple chronic conditions, with caregiver-as-co-equal-participant design, mild-cognitive-impairment-aware communication, geriatric-specific protocols, fall-prevention coordination, hospital-and-skilled-nursing-facility transition orchestration, and integration with home-health, durable-medical-equipment, and community-services networks.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2673[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2674[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Hospice-and-palliative-care coordination assistant.** A specialty variant for patients in the final months of life, with goals-of-care conversation support, comfort-care protocol coordination, family-caregiver support integration, and tight integration with the hospice team. The scope is narrowed compared to the curative-care variant; the relationship-quality engineering is heightened.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2675[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2676[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Post-emergency-department coordination assistant.** A focused variant for the 7- to 30-day window after an emergency department visit that did not result in admission, with ED-discharge follow-up protocols, primary-care-handoff orchestration, follow-up-appointment scheduling, and seam-detection for the high rate of unrecognized abnormal-finding follow-ups that fall through after ED discharges.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2677[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2678[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Behavioral-health-and-medical coordination assistant.** A specialty variant for patients with serious mental illness and significant medical comorbidity, with bidirectional integration between behavioral-health care and medical care, behavioral-health-specific coordination protocols, 42 CFR Part 2 compliance where applicable, and tight integration with both the behavioral-health team (recipe 11.8) and the medical care team. The scope and consent posture are more complex than either standalone variant.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2679[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2680[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Substance-use-disorder coordination assistant.** A specialty variant for patients in substance-use treatment, with 42 CFR Part 2 compliance, medication-assisted-treatment coordination, recovery-network navigation, and tight integration with addiction-medicine providers. Subject to the dense privacy and consent regulations around substance-use treatment.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2681[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2682[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Chronic-kidney-disease coordination assistant.** A focused variant for patients across the CKD progression spectrum, with stage-specific protocols, dialysis-modality decision support coordination (where the patient is choosing among in-center hemodialysis, peritoneal dialysis, transplant evaluation, conservative management), vascular-access coordination for hemodialysis patients, and tight integration with nephrology, vascular surgery, and transplant programs.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2683[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2684[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Diabetes-with-multiple-comorbidities coordination assistant.** A focused variant for diabetes patients with significant comorbidities (cardiovascular disease, chronic kidney disease, retinopathy risk, neuropathy, foot-care needs), with diabetes-specific care-coordination protocols, multi-specialty referral tracking, and integration with the diabetes-care team plus relevant specialists.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2685[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2686[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Multi-language deployment beyond English plus Spanish.** Per-language asset development reviewed by clinical leadership and language-services teams, with per-language equity monitoring.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2687[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2688[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Voice-channel deployment.** A voice-channel variant for patients without smartphones, patients with disabilities affecting written communication, patients who prefer voice (often older adults). Voice-specific design includes slower pacing, briefer responses, and accessibility considerations.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2689[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2690[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Caregiver-channel-only variant.** A variant where the primary user is the caregiver rather than the patient, with caregiver-specific content, caregiver-burden-tracking, respite-resource navigation, and explicit caregiver-as-product-owner design. The patient receives appropriate care from the human team; the assistant supports the caregiver in their coordination role.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2691[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2692[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Risk-stratified-tier deployment.** A multi-tier variant where high-risk patients receive higher-touch engagement (daily, with rapid escalation), medium-risk patients receive medium-touch engagement (weekly, with standard escalation), and lower-risk patients receive lighter-touch engagement (monthly, with reactive support). Risk stratification feeds the engagement intensity, the seam-detection sensitivity, and the human-workforce-attention prioritization.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2693[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2694[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Specialty-population variants.** Veterans (with VA integration where applicable), LGBTQ+ populations (with culturally-affirming content and provider-network integration), racial- and ethnic-minority populations (with culturally-adapted content reviewed by community advisors), incarcerated populations (with specific consent and privacy considerations), populations with limited English proficiency (with extended language coverage), populations with disabilities (with extended accessibility design).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2695[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2696[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Population-health overlay.** The assistant's outputs feed an institutional population-health dashboard tracking patterns of coordination across the population for quality-measurement, clinical-program-design, and value-based-contract reporting purposes. CMS Star ratings, ACO quality measures, HEDIS, and similar reporting frameworks are supported.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2697[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2698[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Continuous-improvement loop with structured failure-mode labeling.** Beyond per-conversation feedback, the institution runs a structured labeling program where reviewers (licensed clinicians, care managers) tag failure modes (out-of-scope, ungrounded-claim, stale-data-claim, scope-violation, role-or-tone-failure, citation-gap, equity-disparity, integration-coverage-gap-undisclosed). The labels feed the protocol-library, seam-detection-rule, prompt-tuning, integration-coverage, and policy-revision workflows.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2699[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2700[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Care-team-augmentation deployment.** The assistant is deployed as an adjunct to specific care teams' practices, with the care team's review of all assistant interactions, the care team's input into the patient's coordination protocols, and the care team's incorporation of assistant-derived data into their practice work. Architectural extensions include care-team-side tooling for review and customization.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2701[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2702[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Multi-institution-shared deployment.** The assistant operates across a regional network of institutions sharing infrastructure (HIE backbone, common protocols, shared workforce capacity), with per-institution governance and per-patient consent-controlled visibility. The architectural complexity increases substantially; the population-level coordination value also increases.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2703[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2704[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Payer-deployed coordination overlay.** The assistant is deployed by the payer for its members rather than by the provider for its patients, with provider-side notification and consent flows. The data sources are different (claims-heavy rather than EHR-heavy), the regulatory posture is different, and the provider-payer relationship management is its own engineering and operational discipline.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2705[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2706[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **TEFCA-participating cross-organizational coordination.** A deployment leveraging TEFCA Qualified Health Information Network (QHIN) participation for cross-organizational data exchange, with the corresponding regulatory and operational discipline. <!-- TODO: verify; TEFCA participation is a maturing framework and specific operational implications continue to evolve -->
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2707[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2708[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
