[49m[38;5;10m+    2709[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2710[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Related Recipes
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2711[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2712[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 11.1 (FAQ Chatbot):** Same chapter, foundational. The coordination assistant inherits the input-screening pipeline, scope filtering, conversation logging, audit pattern, persona discipline, and per-cohort monitoring.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2713[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 11.2 (Appointment Scheduling Bot):** Same chapter. The assistant's recommendations to schedule referral visits, post-discharge follow-ups, and care-transition appointments hand off to the scheduling bot's booking infrastructure.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2714[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 11.3 (Prescription Refill Request Bot):** Same chapter. Conversations surfacing medication-refill needs route to the refill workflow; medication-list reconciliation in the coordination assistant feeds the refill bot's authoritative-medication-list awareness.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2715[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 11.4 (Pre-Visit Intake Bot):** Same chapter. The coordination assistant's longitudinal context can pre-populate intake for scheduled visits with consent.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2716[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 11.5 (Insurance Benefits Navigator):** Same chapter. Conversations surfacing benefits-coverage questions, prior-authorization questions, or out-of-network referral concerns route to the benefits navigator.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2717[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 11.6 (Symptom Checker / Triage Bot):** Same chapter. Acute-symptom presentations during coordination conversations route to the triage workflow with the longitudinal context preserved.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2718[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 11.7 (Chronic Disease Management Coach):** Same chapter. Patients with chronic conditions may have both deployments; the coach handles condition-specific behavior change and biometric coaching, the coordinator handles cross-clinician navigation. Cross-bot integration is high-value.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2719[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 11.8 (Mental Health Support Bot):** Same chapter. Mental-health-crisis disclosures during coordination conversations route to the mental-health pathway. Multi-condition patients with mental-health comorbidity may have both deployments with consent-gated context sharing.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2720[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 11.10 (Clinical Trial Recruitment Conversationalist):** Same chapter. Patients in coordination programs may receive trial-eligibility conversation with appropriate consent.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2721[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 2.5 (After-Visit Summary Generation):** Chapter 2. After-visit summaries feed the coordination assistant's longitudinal context as authoritative records of what happened in each encounter.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2722[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 2.6 (Clinical Note Summarization):** Chapter 2. Summarization of clinical notes powers the assistant's chart-context-summary tool with appropriate sensitivity.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2723[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 2.7 (Discharge Summary Generation):** Chapter 2. Discharge summaries feed the post-discharge transition-of-care workflow as the authoritative discharge plan.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2724[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 3.5 (Hospital Readmission Risk Detection):** Chapter 3. Readmission-risk scores inform the coordination assistant's intensity, the seam-detection sensitivity, and the care-team-attention prioritization.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2725[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 3.7 (Patient Deterioration Early Warning):** Chapter 3. Deterioration-pattern detection complements clinical-side detection systems; coordination-context detection identifies patients at risk of readmission, ED utilization, or care-transition failure.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2726[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 4.5 (Medication Adherence Intervention Targeting):** Chapter 4. Adherence-intervention targeting feeds the coordination assistant's engagement intensity for medication-adherence support.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2727[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 4.7 (Care Management Program Enrollment):** Chapter 4. Care-management program enrollment identifies patients appropriate for the coordination assistant deployment.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2728[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 5.x (Entity Resolution / Record Linkage):** Chapter 5. Patient-record linkage across organizations is the architectural floor for cross-organizational coordination; the assistant operates on linked records.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2729[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 7.1+ (Predictive Analytics / Risk Scoring):** Chapter 7. Risk scores including readmission-risk, fall-risk, frailty, and total-cost prediction inform coordination intensity and prioritization.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2730[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 10.5 (Patient-Facing Voice Assistant):** Chapter 10. Voice-channel coordination support builds on voice-assistant ASR/TTS patterns.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2731[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 12.x (Time Series Analysis):** Chapter 12. Time-series analysis of vital signs, weights, and other tracked measures benefits from temporal pattern recognition and contributes to seam-detection sensitivity.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2732[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 13.x (Knowledge Graphs / Ontology):** Chapter 13. The cross-organizational coordination state benefits from graph-based representation of patient, clinician, organization, condition, medication, and care-event entities and their relationships.
