[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2817[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Estimated Implementation Time
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2818[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2819[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Tier | Scope | Time |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2820[0m:[38;5;10m[49m |------|-------|------|
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2821[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Basic | Single transition-of-care protocol (typically post-acute hospital discharge for heart-failure or COPD), single language (English), single channel (in-app chat), curated coordination-protocol library reviewed by clinical leadership for the chosen protocol, basic seam-detection rule library (10-30 rules), basic provenance-journal discipline, basic caregiver identity model with full proxy-access only, basic consent posture for a single state of residence, integration with the institution's primary EHR via FHIR plus one home-health agency plus one pharmacy chain, basic care-management workflow integration with the institution's existing nurse case managers, basic per-cohort monitoring at the institutional-aggregate level, basic audit pipeline with coordination-decision-record-journal retention, named clinical-leadership ownership, multi-quarter clinical-content development and validation | 12-18 months |
